rgy" of this iconoclastic, funny, brilliant, and highly innovative writer.Praise for The Collected Poems of Ted Berrigan:"This is a great, great book for all seasons of the mind and heart."—Robert Creeley"Thanks to this invaluable Collected Poems, one can hear, as never before, Ted Berrigan dreaming his dream."—The Nation"The Collected Poems of Ted Berrigan is not only one of the most strikingly attractive books recently published, but is also a major work of 20th-century poetry. . . . It is a book that will darken with the grease of my hands. There is no better way to praise it than by saying, ‘If you enjoy poetry, you should have it.’" —Bloomsbury Review "It’s a must-have, a poetic knockout."—Time Out New York  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAmerican poetryy20th century. 7aPOETRY / General.2bisacsh  aa certain slant of sunlight.  aamerican express.  aanti war poem.  abean spasms.  aclassics.  adial a poem.  adoubts.  aearly poems.  aeaster monday.  afor you.  afrom a secret journal.  aliterature.  alondon air.  amany happy returns.  anew york school.  apenn station.  apeople of the future.  apersonal poem 2.  apersonal poem 9.  apoem in the traditional manner.  apoems.  apoetry.  apost modernism.  aresolution.  arusty nails.  asecond wave.  astring of pearls.  atambourine life.  ated berrigan.  athe secret life of ford madox ford.  athe sonnets.  auncollected poems.  awords for love.1 aBerrigan, Anselm, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBerrigan, Edmund, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNotley, Alice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNotley, Alice, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUni